@NODE Introduction "ForceMode Documentation - Introduction"

@{b}Introduction@{ub}

ForceMode is a screenmode promotion utility which does its job  in  a  quite
different way compared to most similar programs.

ForceMode  is  not  program-based  but screenmode-based. This means that you
only  have  to  set  things  up  once   and   every   program   which   uses
intuition.library  to  open  a screen will automatically behave according to
your settings. And if you don't want all programs to do so, you can  exclude
certain  programs  very easily. This guide will help you get the most out of
ForceMode.

The  main  idea  behind  ForceMode  was  to  eliminate  as  many  interlaced
screenmodes  as  possible  without  having to use the rather blocky and ugly
DblX-lowres modes.  But you can of course also use ForceMode  with  graphics
boards  whose  modes  appear as system screenmodes. Since I have no graphics
board, I haven't tested this and therefore can't give a warranty for  proper
working.

Always  keep  in  mind that I am a man who sometimes makes mistakes and that
you use ForceMode on your own risk, but I haven't had any problems  up  till
now.
@ENDNODE

