@{b}Project-menu@{ub}

    @{" About...    " link BT_About}
    @{" Hide window " link BT_Hide}
    @{" Quit        " link BT_Quit}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Settings "ForceMode Documentation - Settings-menu"

@{b}Settings-menu@{ub}

    @{" Load...    " link Load}
    @{" Save       " link BT_Save}
    @{" Save as... " link SaveAs}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Load "ForceMode Documentation - Load settings..."

@{b}Load settings...@{ub}

A file requester appears where you can choose the settings file to be loaded.
All settings are lost;  if you haven't  saved them yet,  ForceMode warns you
and gives you the opportunity to save them.
@ENDNODE

@NODE SaveAs "ForceMode Documentation - Save settings as..."

@{b}Save settings as...@{ub}

A file requester appears where you can choose the file ForceMode  will  save
your settings to.
@ENDNODE

@NODE CloseOpen "ForceMode Documentation - How to close and open the Preferences window"

@{b}How to close and open the Preferences window@{ub}

You can close the Preferences window:


 ∑ by clicking on the Close gadget of the window
 
 ∑ by clicking on the Iconify gadget of the window
   (the third one from top right)
 
 ∑ by clicking on the Hide gadget
 
 ∑ by pressing the 'H' key
 
 ∑ by selecting the 'Project/Hide window' menu item
 
 ∑ by pressing the 'Esc' key
 
 ∑ using the Commodities Exchange program


You can re-open the Preferences window:


 ∑ by pressing the hotkey as defined in the MUI Preferences program
 
 ∑ by double clicking on the ForceMode application icon
 
 ∑ by restarting ForceMode (ForceMode will only run once at a time, though)
 
 ∑ by selecting the 'Tools/ForceMode' menu item
@ENDNODE

@NODE Changes "ForceMode Documentation - Changes since 1.0"

@{b}Changes since 1.0@{ub}

The following changes are important for you as an user:


Version 1.1:

 ∑ The @{" Menus " link WI_Prefs} have changed.

 ∑ Menu help: click first on a menu item with the left mouse button and then
   press the 'Help'-key to get information about the menu item.

 ∑ The structure of  the settings files  has changed.  You can load old set-
   tings files, but the options aren't loaded and must be set again.
@ENDNODE

